  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the PWA**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the PWA design. The plan is for a minimalist, dark theme with accents of Caterpillar Yellow. I\'m prioritizing the dashboard, which will feature three key cards for real-time prices. The cards will need to be prominent and easily readable.\n\n\n**Refining the App Features**\n\nI\'ve been drilling down on features: daily variation history as a line graph, sourcing real-time rates from reliable APIs (looking at DolarToday, EnParaleloVzla), and a refresh button for manual updates. This requires a full-stack approach to securely fetch live data. Dark theme and PWA aspects are locked in. I\'m leaning toward Recharts for the graph, and Tailwind CSS for styling. I will avoid additional UI dependencies.\n\n\n**Prioritizing API Integration**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the API integration. I\'ve updated the `metadata.json` with a name. The core focus is finding a reliable, free API for USD/VES and USDT/VES exchange rates. I will then implement a `server.ts` to proxy requests and handle CORS. After, I will then implement `App.tsx` and prioritize the dashboard components, including a header with the app title and three key cards displaying USDT/VES, USD/VES, and a possible average rate. Recharts will be my choice for graph implementation.\n\n\n**Executing the Refresh**\n\nI\'m now implementing the refresh button logic and defining the API endpoint. I\'ve updated `metadata.json` with the app\'s name. I\'m starting to build out the backend using `express` to fetch rates, and adjusting `vite.config.ts` for the server script. I\'ll need to define `/api/*` routes for proxy requests. Also, I need to check the API, and potentially use the `criptoya` API. I\'m structuring the files as `src/api.ts`, `src/components/`, and `server.ts`.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 176110529
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
